                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Nokei,
<br />

<br />
Even if SOE can compensate the enchanter class to make it useful again, they cant give us back the reason why alot of us played the class.  Alot of us rolled the enchanter for many different reason, but most of us got hooked by what we found we could do in lguk, Sol B, Karnors and Sebilis.  Being able to pull a victory against overwhelming odds became the main reason why I continued to play.  As hard as it is for me to say it, those days are gone....forever. 
<br />

<br />
The diversity of the class is also gone.  We use to be able to handle a train with many different techniques....some of us would load 2 stuns then mez....some of us would use AE mez...some of us would charm to help take a mob out of action while increasing the dps to kill the adds before the cleric went oom....we could also help nuke, again to help eliminate the mobs before the healers went oom....sometimes in tough fight when the tank went down, we could lock down 5 or 6 mobs while the cleric rez the tank back in...and we all had different ways to do it.  Alot of us used our anmination/pet as a "doppleganger"...take aggro for the few seconds it would allow us to escape to lock down that add.  Now we are being forced to play in more of a restricted style...all of us are being force to play the same way, because alot of our techniques are gone (stun, fear, AE mez, charm and even mez).  Charm breaks in the old days did not wipe your group, today it will.  Mez resists didnt kill you outright and a good cleric can heal you even with multiple mobs on you....today a cleric cant even heal you with one mob on you in time....the mob can one round many of us.
<br />

<br />
Their design philosopy has doomed our class.  Sure they may end up compensating our class....but they cant give us back the reason many of us play this class (at least the ones that started before kunark).
<br />

<br />
Skil</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
