                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Without getting hung up over details just yet, I'll just say I like the idea. A whole lot more than I like better buffs.
<br />

<br />
I understand those who say if they can't CC any more they're done with the game, and I may turn into one of them yet. But I also agree with those who say that the entire evolution of the game means that massive trains are always going to be instant death now, and there's no way SOE is going to change that.
<br />

<br />
Given that, I think it is wise for us to try to carve out a new role for ourselves that we'll actually enjoy playing. And pulling has a lot of the things that made mez fun--you have to respond to your environment, think fast, etc. It's very visible to other players. It requires skill, and a good understanding of the mob AI (if you can call it that). It's not the same every time. In short, it's not boring, at least for me. And from comments on this board I think I'm not alone.
<br />

<br />
So even if you disagree with a "fading memories" type spell, what do you think of making enchanters into a better pulling class? Personally I like the old-style in-camp CC better, but given that CC is now done out-of-camp, it only makes sense for us to be good at it.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
