                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well...
<br />

<br />
We have a use in raids with AE mobs (and by now they all have massive AE dots). Circle of Alendar! Whee!
<br />
Too bad that it's a lvl 70 spell that the average Enchanter can't hope to obtain due to the level of the mobs that drop it, and it's non-droppability in both rune and spell form.
<br />
But that's a different gripe altogether.
<br />

<br />
Also too bad that in one raid you can easily go through 40-60 peridots with it depending on how long the fight is and whether there are other enchies with the spell. 
<br />
Clerics and Necros get the peridots removed, we don't. That is simply not fair, but nevermind.
<br />

<br />
If we can't slow (and trust me, 95% of the time on the epic mobs we *cannot* get a slow to stick with or without tash) and we can't mez (yay for not having those spells as the first ones we get... wtf sony?) and we can't stun at all, nor can we heal in any way, or feed mana, or debuff properly, or... hey, get a shammy. Better slow, better debuff, better cha buff, almost equal haste, plus hp buffs, heals and comes with a pet that does damage, not to mention dots? 
<br />
Why pick an enchie who nukes with sub-standard nukes that get resisted 8 times out of 10 (I just finished getting DT'd by Renux - couldn't get anything to stick) whose slow gets usually resisted at least once or twice even with tash (a sub-par MR debuff compared to shm), who can't mez in the high level zones unless they get lvl 69 spells and relies on root (hello Mr. Shammy man), whose 'pet' isn't commandable unless that ench has spent a ton of aa's on it, and which doesn't exactly hit for much, whose contribution to dps via charm costs the group more than it contributes and whose high level charm spells only work in omens zones, whose stuns went out of whack at the beginning of PoP, and who keeps getting constant resists on mobs that ARE mezzable but highly resistant and as a result gets one rounded by said mob, and hence costs the group mana, time and possibly causes deaths because CC (for enchies) has been effectively reduced to a crapshoot?
<br />

<br />
Not enough with that, we get an epic that has a focus effect for a spell line that has next to no use because it won't effect resists, only mezzes that stick - and those mezzes already have a big blur on them, and a rune that, when it drops and fires a pbae boggle agros more mobs than you had before if you're unlucky (which we tend to be).
<br />
Chance of survival = Nil.
<br />

<br />
SOE if you want us to nuke, then give us the tools to do it with and turn us into wizards.
<br />

<br />
Quote during Renux fight today: [Thu Oct 07 01:40:48 2004] (Wizard) tells the group, 'you have a lure nuke, right?'
<br />

<br />
I was good for one thing in that fight, and one thing only: I took the 30k DT.
<br />
Not my idea of fun.
<br />

<br />
I don't think it can be fixed with one spell.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
