                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is the problem with that solution, and how SoE will combat it.
<br />

<br />
Bards, from what I have seen - have 4 methods of preservation.
<br />

<br />
1) Run and mez an add, or just run away (insanely usefull, I LOVE to be able to do that, even if it was only a 15 second mez =P)  (0 mana, can be done anytime)
<br />
2) Fade 800 mana, instant recast...usually the only thing a bard needs mana for at this point in the game anyway.
<br />
3) Deftdance - dodges all hits, reuse time 1 hour.  Useful from front only.
<br />
4) Shield of Notes.  6k rune, recast every 30 min.  Yes folks.  6k rune.
<br />

<br />
Monks, have 2 methods.
<br />
1) FD
<br />
2) Whirlwind.  Very similar to bard deftdance as stated above.
<br />

<br />
Chanters, technically - have more methods than both.
<br />
1) Soothing Words (I agree, dangerous - and the recast time crap)
<br />
2) Mind over Matter (Currently bugged, I think it sorta sucks anyway)
<br />
3) Color Shock ( F - U sony.  I want my 12 aa back =P)
<br />
4) Eldrich Rune (it's cool, but now - with mob difficulty scaled up..it's meh)
<br />
5) Doppleganer (very useful in many places, can also be totally blown if not used properly .  Also, reuse time is crap.  Advanced levels are crap)
<br />
6) Ethereal Rune/Arcane Rune (Granted not an "oh fark" ability, but an ability that no other classes possessed until recently (with bard shield of notes aa)
<br />
7) An animation.  Who at times - can get you out of a pinch.  I've been quite pleased with the most recent one.
<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> Mem blur/Enhanced Forgetfullness.  If you're totally desperate, and angry =P  Works great with EF5
<br />

<br />
So, 6 actual abilities that were implemented to "save us" in those times of need...and 2 spells, that are relatively class specific...and were also instated for the exact same reason those.  I'm confident in saying we have 8 ways of dealing with mob aggro (which seems to be peoples largest beef since GoD/OoW)
<br />

<br />
None of these are good enough &gt;&lt;  Would write more, but gotta work bleh</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
