                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1.  On Fade and improved survivability on resists  
<br />

<br />
To a lesser extent, enchanters already "kind of have" a functional solution in Beguiling Visage.  On Inc, if you hit BV, you can tash immediately upon the mob being engaged and clicky slow it in a heart beat with a minimal chance of pulling the mob off the tank.  - It is a bit of an unconventional method, but it works.
<br />

<br />
2.  On raid functionality, being a raid wizard but enchanter when not raiding, I can certainly relate to people exploding as soon as the tank drops - I am usually one of the first to go, even before the clerics, because a wizard who is doing his/her job stays just below the tanks hate to maximize DPS.  Enchanters have a marginal solution for this as well in Glamorous Visage.  I highly believe an upgrade to ths spell is needed since reducing hate by 10% isn't much; however, there have been a few times raiding PoTime where I have chained this on my wizard and just gone ape crazy on nukes with little fear of being summoned allowing me to increase my DPS.
<br />

<br />
3. As far as a true fade goes, you have BoF and ST blurs with AAs to increase the effectiveness of the spell line.  Boggle helps out in a pinch as well though, I think the power of bogglel should be improved or an upgrade to the spell provided as well as a fast cast low mana AE blur as an upgrade to BoF.
<br />

<br />
4.  I never quite understood why necros have a dump and not enchanters being that enchanters are masters of mind magics - enchanters should be able to dump mana more effectively than necros and allow necros to be a DPS/pet class, as they should be. (I'm sure this would not be a popular idea with most enchanters, but it makes sense)
<br />

<br />

<br />
In any event, as I said, I am probably not a conventional enchanter - I love abusing blur and pacification.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ungzaba Bruja
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724977" target="_blank" class="postlink">My Ghetto Gear</a>
<br />
Iriel
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1117785" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Enchanter Alter Ego</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
